## Bash help output
AutoByteus Docker node launcher

Usage:
  autobyteus-docker <command> [options]
  curl -fsSL <script-url> | bash -s -- <command> [options]

Commands:
  start              Pull and start the default Docker node
  start --new        Start a new Docker node with automatic name and ports
  urls               Show Backend, GraphQL, noVNC, VNC, and debug URLs
  ports              Alias for urls
  status             Show managed Docker nodes
  logs               Show Docker logs for a managed node
  stop               Stop one managed Docker node
  stop --all         Stop all managed Docker nodes
  help               Show this help

Options:
  --name <name>      Friendly node name (default: autobyteus-server)
  --tag <tag>        Docker image tag (default: latest)
  --image <image>    Docker image repository or full image ref (default: autobyteus/autobyteus-server)
  --new              Create the next available friendly node name
  --all              Apply stop/status to all managed nodes
  -h, --help         Show this help

State:
  AUTOBYTEUS_DOCKER_STATE_DIR overrides the state directory.
  Default state directory: $HOME/.autobyteus/docker-server
